04/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgarian Regional Development Minister Valentin Tserovski and European Commission Delegation Head Dimitris Kourkoulas officially launched two EU-funded projects Tuesday (3 June). 
The first project, Social Integration, is worth 4.2m euros, and will be financed by the EU Phare programme. 
It aims to improve skills and encourage entrepreneurship among ethnic groups and people with disabilities. 
The second project, Labour Market Initiatives, aims to promote employment opportunities among jobless and disadvantaged people, and support the entrepreneurship and business development of existing small- and medium-sized enterprises. 
It is co-financed by the Bulgarian government and is worth 5.1m euros. 
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 04/06/03, BTA - 03/06/03)
